ique and personal perspective.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aArchitectszUnited StatesvBiography. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Art History. 4aHistory : History. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / Middle Atlantic (DC, DE, MD, NJ, NY, PA).2bisacsh1 aArmstrong, Michael J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWalton, Steven A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847329140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438473291423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438473291/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles